{
  "texts": [
    "This approach, originating from cybernetics and the intersections of psychology, neuroscience, and computer science, has burgeoned in the last few decades, capturing the interest of ML and artificial intelligence researchers [25,26].In practice, the successful application of RL has been demonstrated in various domains such as robotics, game playing, and autonomous vehicles.",
    "For instance, RL has been instrumental in enabling robots to learn complex manipulation tasks and navigation strategies in uncertain environments.",
    "Similarly, in the realm of game playing, RL algorithms have outperformed human experts in games like Go and chess by learning strategies through millions of simulated games.",
    "Autonomous vehicles also leverage RL to make real-time driving decisions, adapting to dynamic traffic conditions and ensuring safety and efficiency on the road.",
    "Furthermore, advanced RL techniques such as Deep RL integrate deep learning with RL to handle high-dimensional state and action spaces."
  ]
}